    <exercise id="fs-id1628356" type="problems-exercises"><problem id="fs-id2125854">
    <para xmlns:q="http://cnx.rice.edu/qml/1.0" id="import-auto-id2189143">A pogo stick has a spring with a force constant of <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mtext>50</m:mtext><m:mi>×</m:mi><m:msup><m:mtext>10</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup><m:mspace width="0.20em"/><m:mtext> N/m</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{2 "." "50" times "10" rSup { size 8{4} } " N/m"} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>, which can be compressed 12.0 cm. To what maximum height can a child jump on the stick using only the energy in the spring, if the child and stick have a total mass of 40.0 kg? Explicitly show how you follow the steps in the <link document="m42151" target-id="fs-id2025907">Problem-Solving Strategies for Energy</link>.</para></problem></exercise>
